0 sc0 ls0 ws0">especially verse 6. </div><div class="t m167 x61 h28 yb7b ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">22. </div><div class="t m144 x5b h28 yb7b ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">What scripture is illustrated by this event ? </div><div class="t ma79 x4a h28 ya92 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Eccl. 9 : 18. </div><div class="t mb68 x6a h28 ya93 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">NOTES. </div><div class="t m823 x61 h28 yd78 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">THE course of Israel in supposing that only a </div><div class="t ma78 x18 h28 y103b ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">few men would be sufficient to capture Ai, shows </div><div class="t m597 x4a h28 ybd8 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">that they expected to take it simply by force of </div><div class="t m96c x18 h28 yb80 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">arms, and that they were not depending on the </div><div class="t m818 x18 h28 y100a ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">help of the Lord. It did not matter if Ai was a </div><div class="t m9b8 x18 h28 y103c ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">very small city compared with Jericho, there was </div><div class="t m5d2 x18 h28 ye12 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">as much reason for taking a large force of men to </div><div class="t me4 x4a h28 ye7f ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">capture it as there was at Jericho. Since the Lord </div><div class="t me61 x4a h28 y103d ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">threw down the walls, Jericho could have been </div><div class="t m476 x18 h28 y103e ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">taken with a few men as well as with the thousands </div><div class="t m48d x18 h28 ya19 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">who surrounded it. The Lord could have delivered </div><div class="t m51 x4a h28 yf4f ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Ai into the hands of the three thousand Israelites </div><div class="t m20f x4a h28 ydbc ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">who went up to take it, as easily as into the hands </div><div class="t m628 x18 h28 y103f ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">of tens of thousands, since it is nothing with him to </div><div class="t m9f5 x4a h28 ydbf ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">help &quot;whether with many, or with them that have </div><div class="t m188 x4a h28 y732 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">no power&quot; (2 Chron. 14 : z t); but the Lord had </div><div class="t meab x4a h28 y804 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">not told them to take only a few men, and their </div><div class="t m863 x4a h28 y82e ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">doing so showed that they thought themselves fully </div><div class="t m1b0 x18 h28 y82f ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">able to help themselves. Perhaps they had become </div><div class="t ma75 x4a h28 ye04 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">unduly elated and vainglorious over the wonder- </div></div><div class="pi" data-data='{"ctm":[1.000000,0.000000,0.000000,1.000000,0.000000,0.000000]}'></div></div>
